PN,41102
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F411A1775837470
OL,3,CEurotunnel fined #2.5m after heavy
OL,4,Clighting carriage fell on surveyor
OL,6,FChannel Tunnel Group Ltd (CTGL), also
OL,7,Fknown as Eurotunnel, failed to take
OL,8,Fmeasures to ensure the lighting masts
OL,9,Fwere safe and without health risks,
OL,10,Fthe Office for Road and Rail (ORR)
OL,11,Ffound on Friday.
OL,13,FEurotunnel, which pleaded guilty, had
OL,14,Fbreached its duty under the Health and
OL,15,FSafety at Work etc. Act 1974 as it was
OL,16,Fin control of lighting mast
OL,17,Fmaintenance, associated equipment and
OL,18,Fwhere it was situated, the independent
OL,19,Fregulator found.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/6
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,412,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41103
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F411A1775837470
OL,3,CEurotunnel fined #2.5m after heavy
OL,4,Clighting carriage fell on surveyor
OL,6,FHM chief inspector of railways Richard
OL,7,FHines said there were occasions when
OL,8,Flighting carriages were being "winched
OL,9,Fup and down by staff who had not been
OL,10,Fappropriately trained".
OL,12,FHe added: "This catalogue of what were
OL,13,Fentirely preventable maintenance and
OL,14,Fplanning errors led to a truly
OL,15,Fhorrific incident, and my thoughts are
OL,16,Fwith the injured person and their
OL,17,Ffamily for the pain and suffering the
OL,18,Fincident caused, and continues to
OL,19,Fcause.
OL,26,@pD@_OUrD@VO]tD@KOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/6
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,412,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41104
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F411A1775837470
OL,3,CEurotunnel fined #2.5m after heavy
OL,4,Clighting carriage fell on surveyor
OL,6,F"It is quite simply astonishing to
OL,7,Flearn that there were occasions where
OL,8,Flighting carriages were winched up and
OL,9,Fdown by staff who had not been
OL,10,Fappropriately trained, without a
OL,11,Fsuitable safe system of work, that
OL,12,Fthere was no effective preventative
OL,13,Fmaintenance of the lighting mast and
OL,14,Fits equipment, and that there was a
OL,15,Flack of an appropriate risk assessment
OL,16,Ffor that specific task.
OL,26,@nD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/6
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,412,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41105
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F411A1775837470
OL,3,CEurotunnel fined #2.5m after heavy
OL,4,Clighting carriage fell on surveyor
OL,6,F"This case serves as another reminder
OL,7,Fto industry that regular maintenance
OL,8,Fof equipment and thorough and
OL,9,Fappropriate risk assessments in
OL,10,Fcarrying out works is crucial to help
OL,11,Fprevent a repeat of such an event.
OL,13,F"The ruling added that the outcome
OL,14,Fcould have been worse had the
OL,15,Fstructure's fall not been broken by
OL,16,Fobjects lying around the site.
OL,18,FThe Channel Tunnel is over 30 years
OL,19,Fold, having been opened by Queen
OL,20,FElizabeth II and then French president
OL,21,FFrancois Mitterrand in 1994.
OL,26,@nD@AOUuD@AO]}D@E{q
